<br>
Court case- Soundly convicted in a very quick trial in which he barely offered a defense.  Sentenced to be put to death.  Spends many years on death row. <br>
<br>
Time machine (to the late late 90's)<br>
<br>
Still on death row this man and his lawyer suddenly become part of the limelight again in their little area.  For one of the deceased jury member's brother claimed that during his trial his sister was insane and talking to her dead uncle.  He claims that he told her on multiple occasions how their dead uncle told her to convict him to make him a martyr.<br>
<br>
Result, another appeal after all the other have been exhausted.<br>
<br>
Result of appeal is motion for a new trial, (still wasn't decided last time my family updated me).<br>
<br>
Problem is that the 2 material witnesses are dead.  All the the evidence such as the gun and whatnot that were used in the original trial are gone.  There is almost no possible way that with a new trial he will be convicted because the evidence of the crime no longer exists.<br>
<br>
